id: pm-zyez
title: "Sentry PM-CLI-1R: 'cannot add command init as already have command init' — top-level init double-registration throws raw Commander error"
description: "Production Sentry issue PM-CLI-1R (org unbrained, id 128405024), last seen 2026-06-16, level=error, unresolved. Raw 'Error: cannot add command init as already have command init' — NOT a CommandError, so it is OUTSIDE the Sentry release-gate expected-CLI-error allowlist and can block the daily auto-release (the exact fragility pm-nb08 warns about)."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[3]: cli,observability,reliability
created_at: "2026-06-17T06:05:47.354Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-17T06:05:47.354Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-ugqx
body: "## Stack trace (Sentry latest event)\n\nculprit: Command._registerCommand (commander)\nrunPmCli -> registerCoreCommandFamilies -> registerSetupCommands -> Command.command -> Command._registerCommand\n\n## Root cause\n\nsrc/cli/register-setup.ts:330-332 `registerSetupCommands(program)` does `program.command('init')`. Commander throws when `program` ALREADY has a top-level `init` command at that point. Reproduces in production but not in tests, so the prior `init` registration is workspace-dependent — most likely an installed extension/package whose manifest declares a top-level command named `init`, or the bootstrap executable-alias rewrite (pm-7by2) resolving an alias to `init` before core registration. (Note: register-setup.ts:209 `.command('init')` is the `pm extension/package init` SUBcommand and is a different scope — not the collision.)\n\n## Impact\n\n- Unhandled raw Error reaches Sentry as a high-severity unresolved event.\n- Because the title is not a `CommandError:`/standup-export pattern, it is not allowlisted by the release Sentry gate (release-automation-contract.spec.ts) and can fail the gate -> silently block the daily auto-release (pm-nb08 class of failure).\n\n## Proposed fix (separate PR)\n\n- Guard top-level command registration against built-in name collisions: before `program.command('init')`, detect an existing `init` (program.commands) and either skip or throw a normalized PmCliError with an actionable message (which extension declared the colliding command + how to rename/disable).\n- Add a regression test that pre-registers a top-level `init` then runs registerSetupCommands and asserts a clean PmCliError (not a raw Commander throw).\n- Consider extending the extension command-registration path to reject/parenthesize names that shadow built-in top-level commands.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Sentry: PM-CLI-1R / 128405024 (unbrained)\n- src/cli/register-setup.ts:330-332 (top-level init registration)\n- Related: pm-nb08 (auto-release Sentry-gate fragility), pm-yohx (count-agnostic allowlist)"
